snippet.textDisplay:
I look at this circus and wonder. Are people really so blind?
First, they show to the side how the rocket takes off, then after the destruction itself they move the camera "supposedly attached to the rocket."
So, you need to show this camera from 1 second of flight, otherwise, it looks even worse than computer graphics, it does not even reach the level of a movie!
Move on. The video shows before the explosion that the rocket begins to jump (like waves), after which the explosion is to distract our attention, and at this moment the front of the hull is completely brought in, which is symbolized by the waves around the front of the rocket. Those who have ever seen a boat from a drone will obviously find a 99% similarity. And that's not all! Pay attention to the fragment of the rocket, which floats up from our main object of attention - it moves crookedly as if hinting to us that it is beating on water and is now drowning.
I’m all leading to this. There is a video on the Internet that says that space consists of water, and where an example of the flight of the same Nas is given. And one gets the feeling that NASA just decided to somehow block the moment, and show that - the rocket really exploded, and something flew further. But I assure you, no one has ever flown either to the moon or in principle to space. Even the wives of the astronauts spoke of this. And all these missile tests are just a screen for believers in space. How can one believe in space, even if not all the continents on Earth are still open, or open, but carefully hidden? It's ridiculous!
